g.text: How does baahu know which machines should rerender?
machines A, B, C, and F listen to this event... but after transitioning, machine A no longer
renders machine C. How can we avoid doing any work for machine C (transition, effects, rendering)?
every virtual node tracks its depth in the tree. after a global event,
baahu sorts, then renders, the relevant machines by node depth. this
method ensures that parents render before their children.
baahu never created and diffed virtual nodes for machine C. machines D and E
didn't listen to this event, so they were not rerendered either.
